OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Deputy Labour leader Angela Rayner has 
OL,6, told of her distress at repeated abuse 
OL,7, including threats to "hunt her down"   
OL,8, like murdered MP Jo Cox.               
OL,10,FSpeaking at length about the issue for 
OL,11,Fthe first time, the Ashton-under-Lyne  
OL,12,FMP told the BBC the harassment began   
OL,13,Fwhen she took on the role in 2020.     
OL,15,FBenjamin Iliffe was sentenced to 15    
OL,16,Fweeks in prison for sending Ms Rayner a
OL,17,Fthreatening email in October.          
OL,19,FMs Rayner said she had now "got used to
OL,20,Fthe abuse, which was sad in itself".   
